the most common conditions are that many government officials who administrate an industry also take charge of the enterprises in the same industry .
therefore , they are able to take full advantage of their right or power to offer preferential conditions on contracts , loans , and taxes to these enterprises .
these phenomena ruined the fair market competition ; in turn it obstructed china &apos;s transformation of from planned economy to market economy .
it is understood that , over 500 largest state-owned enterprises originally attached to the party , government , and judicatory departments will be supervised by a newly established commission under the state council , and the employees of these enterprises will be arranged by personal departments .
