russia faced with population crisis
moscow , june . 20 ( xinhua , xie rong ) -- death rate of russians have exceeded the birth rate for the past 10 consecutive years with an annual decrease of 2 million from its population , which poses a population crisis to russia , said y. jadekov , vice health minister of the russian government on 20th .
in the past 10 years , the death rate of able-bodied male citizens is especially high , jadekov was quoted by itar-tass as saying in the economic forum meeting held in st. petersburg .
besides , in russia , the dominant families composed by parents and two children have given way to families composed by parents and one child and the number of no-child families has also increased greatly .
he points out that the population senility problem of the russian society will be in years .
he says that faced with such severe situation , the russian government should carry out an economic population policy targeted at society nationwide , so as to improve the living quality of common russian families .
he suggests that the government formulate policies to attract foreign labor immigrants and create better living conditions for them .
according to jadekov &apos; , the general health deterioration of the russian citizens attributes to the main reason of death rate increase of the russian population in the past 10 years .
during this period , the number of russian citizens suffering from various diseases increased greatly .
